survey_response.review_text:
I lost a portion of my 20 year old cavity filled molar tooth while eating dinner and wanted to get it addressed at the earliest. Honestly I was looking for a dentist close to my home so that I could make multiple visits easily, if required. A quick Google map search, and I figured that not only is Dr. Rupali's clinic closest to my home, its even the one with the highest rated reviews.

Dr. Rupali is very warm and approachable. She listened to my case and inspected my tooth. Next she brings up a piece of paper and illustrates my tooth, the issue and the options to fix it. She tells me the two options, the pros and cons and which is cost effective. 

Dr. Rupali is methodical in her approach and ensures that he team adheres to her instructions. Before starting the procedure, she tells me in case I feel pain or discomfort to alert her and she will administer anaesthesia. However throughout the procedure I did not feel any pain and the whole procedure completed without any discomfort. Dr. Rupali is very patient and ensured the reconstruction was done perfectly. My session lasted for half an hour and I felt like I got my natural tooth back.

One point worth mentioning is that I had been to the clinic with my seven year old daughter. Dr Rupali made sure my daughter sat in the doctor's cabin during my procedure rather than the waiting lobby. This goes to show her compassion and presence of mind. I'm really thankful to Dr. Rupali's service and would not hesitate to recommend her to anyone requiring an experienced dentist for effective treatment. Thank you Dr. Rupali!

survey_response.review_text: I had been a decade that I had visited a dentist. Recently I was having severe unbearable dental pain from some days. When I had a visit to the clinic, I was explained in detail what is the root cause and how it can be resolved. The doctor explained that I has periodontitis issue and it was recommended to have a Dental Surgery. The clinic is well equipped and also specialists visited for recommendation. My Dental Surgery as done by a Periodontal Specialist. Days later I had a speedy recovery. Followed by the Surgery, I was also having a zigzag arrangement of teeth which was enhancing the plaque deposition. When asked how to resolve this issue, the doctor explained the process and also made prototype models to explain how it will look after correction. The doctor termed this as Smile Design. This was performed by Extraction, Root Canal followed placement of Bridge. After years, I feel that I can smile freely (previously, as the front teeth were zigzag I was not comfortable to have a wide smile). I acknowledge the doctor for kind of guidance and treatment. Also, a lots of respect for the knowledge and experience in handling the treatment.  Thanks to the doctor for giving me a confident Smile :-)
